Information:

Docker -> Postgre connection:
1. Install image of docker
2. docker run -d --name postgre -p 5432:5432 -v pg-data:/var/lib/postgresql/data postgres:latest
	-> -d (run as deamon)
	-> --name postgre (give name to container)
	-> -p 5432:5432 (from which port to which port)
	-> -v pg-data:/var/lib/postgresql/data (in which volume it will be used)
	-> postgres:latest (container Id)
3. docker exec -it postgre /bin/sh (get in the container inside)
4. psql -U postgres (inside the postgresql, now create table etc)
5. docker inspect <container_id>
6. Take IP and login via pgadmin
